headline: Does CBRE’s Pearce Deal And Leadership Shuffle Recast Its Services-Led Investment Story (CBRE)?
summary: CBRE Group recently expanded its retail and property management leadership, naming Caroline Main as UK head of retail and appointing Darrell Palasciano to lead retail services in Charlotte, while also arranging over 100,000 square feet of new and renewed leases at a redeveloped Andover, Massachusetts campus. These moves, alongside the acquisition of Pearce Services for about US$1.20 billion and a US$750.00 million senior notes issuance, highlight CBRE’s push to deepen service capabilities...
